16
00:01:04,080 --> 00:01:10,100
To pronounce the /eɪ/ vowel, you should focus on the correct position of your lips and tongue.

17
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:13,000
Partially open your mouth,

18
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:17,020
spread your lips wide and make them tense.

19
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:26,040
Raise the middle of your tongue to the roof of your mouth and push it to the front.

20
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:33,520
The tip of your tongue should be down, just behind your bottom front teeth.

21
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:43,640
Remember, the /eɪ/ is a tense sound, so your lips and your tongue should be very tense.

22
00:01:44,220 --> 00:01:47,520
Your jaw should be partially lowered.

23
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:51,600
Now, let’s pronounce this sound:

24
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:52,840
/eɪ/

25
