35
00:04:34,040 --> 00:04:37,440
The /eɪ/ is one of the major vowel sounds of American English,

36
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:43,200
and it’s also the pronunciation of the first letter of the English alphabet.

37
00:04:43,860 --> 00:04:49,380
So, when you hear the /eɪ/ sound, you can assume that it should be spelled with the letter “a.”

38
00:04:49,820 --> 00:04:52,980
And you will be right, but only 73% of the time.

39
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:58,060
The remaining 27% is divided by the following combination of letters:

40
00:04:58,060 --> 00:05:02,740
such as “ai,” as in “wait,”

41
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:06,660
“ay,” as in “day,”

42
00:05:07,220 --> 00:05:10,300
“ei,” as in “eight”

43
